[1] El Salvador
Date: 20 Sep 2006
From: ProMED <promed@promedmail.org>
Source: Diario Co Latino, El Salvador [Trans. Mod.TY, edited]
<http://www.diariocolatino.com/nacionales/detalles.asp?NewsID=13863>

The Minister of Health, Guillermo Maza, confirmed this morning [20
Sep 2006] another fatal case of dengue. An 11-month-old infant was
victim number 4 in the epidemic this year. The child, who came from
the Mejicanos Municipality, died 1 Aug [2006] in the Benjamin Bloom
Children's Hospital.
The Minister emphasized the role of the population in eradication of
dengue and that it was vital that the number of cases of this disease
did not increase.
Official statistics indicate that 195 people have had DHF and 6497
have had classical dengue fever this year [2006]. At present, 3
departments [state equivalents Mod.TY] are under "red alert:"
Sonsonate, La Libertad y San Salvador, due to a significant increase
in dengue cases and especially DHF.
Nonetheless, [Minister] Mazo indicated that there has been a decrease
in cases and discarded the need to take stronger measures to combat
mosquito breeding places in Santa Ana and San Vicente, which have not
reported an increase in cases in recent days.
The Epidemiological surveillance report indicates that 17 244
suspected classical dengue fever cases and 316 [suspected] DHF cases
have received medical attention [this year 2006].
--
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>
[Does dengue virus type 3 continue to be the main, or only, serotype
circulating in this epidemic? A map of El Salvador can be accessed at:
