[2] Brazil (Ribeirao Preto)
Date: 16 Sep 2006
From: ProMED-PORT <Promed-Port@promedmail.org>
Source: Jornal A Cidade [edited]
<http://www.jornalacidade.com.br/geral>

Ribeirao Preto [Sao Paulo State] is 3rd in dengue cases
-----------------------------------------------
Ribeirao Preto, with 3283 cases of dengue, is experiencing the worst
epidemic of this disease in its history. In the ranking of the State
Secretary of Health, this city occupies 3rd place after Catanduva and
Sao Jose do Rio Preto. According to data collected as of 8 Sep
[2006], Ribeirao Preto had 2888 cases, versus 3055 in Catanduva, and
7841 in Rio Preto.
Due to the seriousness of the situation, the Municipal Secretary of
Health, Oswaldo Cruz Franco, issued this alert, "The situation is
very dangerous. The population has not eliminated [mosquito] breeding
sites, and when the rains begin, we run the risk that the epidemic
will become worse.
A Breteau [vector] survey will begin in October 2006. The Division of
Vector Control intends to initiate, in the 2nd half of October 2006,
the year's 2nd Breteau index [BI] survey in Ribeirao Preto. This
indicator measures the number of [containers harboring] dengue vector
mosquito larvae [_Aedes aegypti_] for each 100 premises [inspected]
and is important for officials working to prevent or combat dengue.
In July 2006, when the 1st survey was made, Ribeirao Preto had an
index of 2.3, considered high by [the standards set by] the World
Health Organization, which sets limits at 0 to 1.
Jardim Recreio and Lagoinha lideram had BIs of 5.2 and 5.1,
respectively. Alto da Boa Vista and Sumare, in the south region, had
BIs of 4.5.
--
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>
