[4] Cuba
Date: 24 Sep 2006
From: ProMED-PORT <Promed-Port@promedmail.org>
Source: La Jornada [Trans. Mod.TY, edited]
<http://www.jornada.unam.mx>

The Cuban government today [24 Sep 2006] confirmed that dengue is a
resurgent public health problem, and that they have not been able to
stop the life cycle of the vector, but maintain silence about the
numbers of cases and the area affected by this disease.
The interim President, Raul Castro, headed up a meeting of provincial
governors, some of whom criticized the status of the massive battle
in recent weeks. [The government] will not rest until this dangerous
vector has been eradicated, according to today's [23 Sep 2006]
official daily newspaper, Granma. This newspaper indicated that the
Minister of Health, Jose Ramon Balaguer, reported [on the outbreak],
but did not report what he said.
--
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>
[This is the 1st report quoting an official Cuban government source.
ProMED hopes that other official reports will follow, indicating the
extent and intensity of the epidemic and the progress of the vector
control campaign. - Mod.TY]
